@startuml
' Auto-derived 2026-04-29 from transaction-service (LedgerCommandListener,
' TransactionService, Outbox), notification-service TransferEventListener,
' audit-service SecurityAuditListener.
' Counterpart of: docs/diagrams/sequences/02_sequence_money_transfer.puml
title Sequence 02 — Internal Money Transfer (current, RabbitMQ + Outbox + Saga)

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam participantFontStyle bold

actor       Customer
participant "React Frontend"        as FE
participant "API Gateway"           as GW
participant "transaction-service"   as TX
database    "transaction_db (PG)"   as DBT
participant "RabbitMQ"              as RMQ
participant "notification-service"  as NOTIF
participant "audit-service"         as AUD
database    "audit_db (Mongo)"      as DBA
participant "SMTP (Gmail)"          as SMTP

Customer -> FE : Transfer form\n{from, to, amount, currency, idempotencyKey}
FE -> GW       : POST /api/transaction_service/.../transfer\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>
GW -> GW       : JwtAuthFilter verifies JWT,\ninjects X-User-Id / X-User-Roles
GW -> TX       : forward (Eureka LB)

activate TX
TX -> RMQ      : publish TransferRequest →\nsaga.commands.queue\n(idempotent on idempotencyKey)
TX --> GW      : 202 Accepted {referenceNumber}
GW --> FE      : 202
FE --> Customer: "Transfer submitted"

== Async (LedgerCommandListener) ==
RMQ -> TX      : saga.commands.queue → handleExecuteTransferCommand
TX -> DBT      : SELECT ledger_balance(source, currency) FOR UPDATE
TX -> DBT      : SELECT ledger_balance(dest,   currency) FOR UPDATE
alt insufficient funds / wallet missing
  TX -> DBT      : INSERT transactions {status=FAILED, failure_reason}
  TX -> DBT      : INSERT outbox_messages (TransferFailedEvent)
  DBT --> TX     : COMMIT
else ok
  TX -> DBT      : UPDATE source.available_balance -= amount\n         dest.available_balance   += amount
  TX -> DBT      : INSERT transactions {status=COMPLETED, version}
  TX -> DBT      : INSERT outbox_messages (TransferSuccessEvent)
  DBT --> TX     : COMMIT
end

TX -> RMQ      : OutboxPoller → publish TransferSuccess/Failed\n(routingKey transfer.success / transfer.failed)
deactivate TX

== Fan-out ==
RMQ -> NOTIF : NOTIFICATION_TRANSFER_EVENTS_QUEUE
activate NOTIF
NOTIF -> NOTIF : TransferEventListener.onTransferEvent\nbranches on routing key
NOTIF -> NOTIF : TransferAlertService.handleSuccess/Failure
NOTIF -> SMTP  : send email (template rendered)
NOTIF -> RMQ   : audit event {action=NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_SENT}
deactivate NOTIF

RMQ -> AUD   : audit.queue
AUD -> DBA   : INSERT security_logs

note over TX, DBT
  Transactional Outbox pattern: business write
  + outbox_messages row commit atomically.
  A poller relays them to RabbitMQ later, so we
  never lose events on broker outage.
end note
@enduml

